I think the question is how `self` is bound, not whether it&#x27;s explicit. If I&#x27;m not mistaken, your example there would work in any language which allows parasitic inheritance (or more generally, where functions are objects with properties). It&#x27;s just that Python is set up so using `self` is a good way to do that.<p>Would this JavaScript not be equivalent?<p><pre><code>  function runAPIMethod(/* expect params for call */) {
      // read cfg
      // do necessary stuff to base object

      // replaces run() method
      var rq = requests.requests(this.method, this._url, [].prototype.slice(arguments, 1));
      [rq.json(), rq.status_code];

  };
  var boundMethod = runAPIMethod.bind(apiInstance);</code></pre>
